gomodel:SYNGO_3833  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Nbea knockout neurons in culture fail to develop a normal number of dendritic spines.\"\nFig.2: \"Selective reduction of axo-spinous synapses in brains of heterozygous Nbea-mutant mice\"\nFig.3: \"Organization of the postsynaptic compartment in absence of Nbea.\"\nFig.4: \"Nbea deletion affects postsynaptic currents in cultured knockout neurons and heterozygous brain slices.\". Experimental description: - \"All experiments involving mice were performed in accordance with local institutional and government regulation for animal welfare. Cultures were prepared from individual hippocampi of wild-type and Nbea KO mouse embryos (E17), digested wit\"" ;
